    "title": "Incubation (Gemini pt. 1)",
    "description": "&quot;The square is not a subconscious form. It is the creation of intuitive reason. The face of the new art. The square is a living, regal infant. The first step of pure creation in art.&quot;\n– Kazimir Malevich\n\n&quot;I am an anarchist in politics and an impressionist in art as well as a symbolist in literature. Not that I understand what these terms mean, but I take them to be all merely synonyms of pessimist.&quot;\n– Henry Adams\n\n&quot;Take the birds which you'll have noticed in so many of my recent paintings. I never thought them up, they just materialized of their own accord; they were born on the canvas... it is absurd to read any sort of symbolic significance into them.&quot;\n– Georges Braque",
